The '''Wake clan''' (和気氏) was a Japanese [[clan]] that bore the name "Wake" as their [[uji|family name]].

The clan was a powerful local family based in {{ill|Wake District, Okayama|ja|和気郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wake District, Okayama|qq=}}, {{ill|Bizen Province|ja|備前国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bizen Province|qq=}}, which was historically called "Fujino District." They claimed descent from {{ill|Nuteshiwake-no-mikoto|ja|鐸石別命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nuteshiwake-no-mikoto|qq=}}, a son of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Suinin|qq=}}. The name was also sometimes written as "Betsu clan" (別氏). Their noble titles ({{ill|Kabane|ja|姓|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kabane|qq=}}) changed over time: they held the title [[Kimi (kabane)|Kimi]] (公), later becoming [[Mahito (kabane)|Mahito]] (真人), [[Sukune (kabane)|Sukune]] (宿禰), and finally, in [[774]] ({{ill|Hōki era|ja|宝亀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōki era|qq=}} 5), they were granted the title [[Asomi|Asomi]] (朝臣).

